### [EXECUTIVE TECHNICAL SUMMARY]
The file `I.b` acts as a **Dependency Container** or **Data Transfer Object (DTO) Wrapper**. It facilitates the coupling between a primary cryptographic/transaction engine (`C0387b`) and an optional, secondary configuration or session management module (`C0392g`). In the context of a payment application, this class is likely used by a factory or injector to instantiate the transaction handler, ensuring that the necessary cryptographic context is injected before a payment request is initiated.

